# JetAuto Pro — Power-On & Connection Guide

## What Happens When You Power On

1. **Flip the power switch.**
2. **Wait 20–30 seconds.** During this time the system boots.
3. **LED1 on the expansion board flashes blue, and the buzzer beeps once.** This indicates both ROS configuration and the device are ready for use. 
4. **The robot defaults to AP Direct Connection mode** and generates a Wi-Fi network starting with "HW", with the default password "hiwonder". 
5. **LiDAR behavior depends on model:** the A1 LiDAR (the model on our unit) starts rotating a short time after power-on and keeps spinning continuously.  Before powering on, push the LiDAR's own switch to "ON" — it has a separate switch from the main robot power. 
6. **If a 7-inch screen is attached,** it shows the system desktop on boot, and on advanced/ultimate kits the robot plays an audio "I'm ready" announcement. 

### If the Wi-Fi hotspot doesn't appear
Re-check the steps above first. If LED1 is solid blue (not flashing), the robot may already be in LAN mode — press and hold the KEY1 button for 5–10 seconds to switch back to AP mode and the HW network should reappear.  If KEY1 doesn't trigger flashing, the SD card/SSD may not be detected — try reseating it.  If the issue persists after all of this, it may be a board-level fault — contact Hiwonder support. 

