## ⚠️ Important Notes Before First Power-On

If the battery voltage is below 10V, charge the robot before operating it.  Keep the robot on a flat surface, away from platform edges, and maintain a safe distance once powered on to avoid injury from unexpected movement.  Avoid letting the robotic arm sit under load for extended periods, as this shortens servo lifespan. 

## Charging

A full charge from 10V to 12.3V takes approximately 3–4 hours.  Always turn off the power switch before charging, and never connect the charger directly to the Jetson Nano's DC port — only to the dedicated power board port, or the board will be damaged.  The charger indicator is red while charging and turns green once full — unplug promptly to avoid overcharging.  If battery voltage drops below 10V during use, the buzzer sounds an alarm. 

